<span id="ix.ccxii-p3"></span>*To Olympius*. <span
id="fr_2798"></span>[2799](#fn_2798.md)

<span id="ix.ccxii-p5"></span><span class="c14"><span
id="ix.ccxii-p5.1"></span>Truly</span> when I read your excellency’s
letter I felt unwonted pleasure and cheerfulness; and when I met your
well-beloved sons, I seemed to behold yourself.  They found me in the
deepest affliction, but they so behaved as to make me forget the
hemlock, which your dreamers and dream mongers are carrying about to my
hurt, to please the people who have hired them.  Some letters I have
already sent; others, if you like, shall follow.  I only hope that they
may be of some advantage to the recipients.

